A BILL TO BE ENTITLED
AN ACT
1 To amend Part 2 of Article 3 of Chapter 1 of Title 40 of the Official Code of Georgia
2 Annotated, relating to certification of motor carriers, so as to repeal the authority of the
3 Department of Public Safety to establish reasonable rates, fares, and charges for
4 transportation by motor carriers of household goods; to provide for related matters; to repeal
5 conflicting laws; and for other purposes.
6 BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF GEORGIA:
7 SECTION 1.
8 Part 2 of Article 3 of Chapter 1 of Title 40 of the Official Code of Georgia Annotated,
9 relating to certification of motor carriers, is amended by repealing in its entirety Code
10 Section 40-1-118, relating to establishment of rates, fares, and charges for transportation of
11 household goods, and designating said Code section as reserved.
12 SECTION 2.
13 Said part is further amended by revising Code Section 40-1-119, relating to charges by motor
14 carriers and unjust discrimination by carriers prohibited, as follows:
